ch capacity. Focusing on the case of an exponential list\nsize $L_n=e^{n \\Theta}$, its comparison with ordinary mismatched decoding shows\nthat the increase in capacity is by $\\Theta$ bits per channel use for all\nchannels and decoding metrics. Several properties of the average error\nprobability in the setup of mismatched list decoding with deterministic list\nsize are provided.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 18 Oct 2018 16:57:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-19"}
